body:
Please remove `World.ObserveAfterWinOrLose` too, then. That was added to prevent the the observer UI from showing for a split second in missions before the video starts, and isn't useful anymore with this. Ideally, loading of the observer UI should be delayed by the `GameOverDelay` defined in `MissionObjectivesInfo` (see diff below), but that causes some weirdness in the radar widget, of all things.

When a lua script errors, the video is still shown before the error dialog pops up.

I'm not really sure if this isn't ultimately a step backwards wrt to what we'll eventually want to do with the score screen, but since we don't have a clearly laid out plan for that, and this will please the score screen haters, I guess I'm overall ok with the way this works. I'm not that fond of the many `IsGameOver` checks sprinkled throughout a load of unrelated traits, though, but don't see any better way either atm, and in principle it's not much different to the `player.WinState` checks found everywhere.

